# UI Simplicity First

Prefer straightforward, readable code over dense or clever code.

- No nested ternaries.
- Prefer early returns/guard clauses to deep branching.
- Avoid mutation when reasonable (`push`, in-place edits, reassignment-heavy flows).
- Use small named helpers for non-trivial conditions, label text, and parsing.
- Keep functions focused: one responsibility per function.
- Prefer pure functions for derivations and formatting logic.
- Keep render trees easy to scan; move logic out of JSX when it grows.

## Example

```ts
// ❌ Dense
const label = saving ? "Saving..." : loading ? "Loading..." : done ? "Done" : "Continue";

// ✅ Clear
function getLabel(params: { saving: boolean; loading: boolean; done: boolean }): string {
  if (params.saving) return "Saving...";
  if (params.loading) return "Loading...";
  if (params.done) return "Done";
  return "Continue";
}
```

